A5: (for ASeq being (SetSequence of S) holds (ASeq is  non-ascending implies (( P1 * ASeq ) is  convergent & ( lim ( P1 * ASeq ) ) = ( P1 . ( Intersection ASeq ) ))))
proof
let ASeq being (SetSequence of S);
assume that
A6: ASeq is  non-ascending;
(for n holds ( 0 ) <= ( ( P1 * ASeq ) . n ))
proof
let n;
reconsider A = ( ASeq . n ) as (Event of S);
(( 0 ) <= ( P1 . A ) & ( dom ( P1 * ASeq ) ) = ( NAT )) by MEASURE1:def 2,SEQ_1:1;
hence thesis by FUNCT_1:12;
end;
then A7: ( P1 * ASeq ) is  bounded_below by RINFSUP1:10;
reconsider F = ASeq as (Function of ( NAT ),S) by CKB4:1;
A8: (for n being (Element of ( NAT )) holds ( F . ( n + 1 ) ) c= ( F . n )) by A6,PROB_2:6;
A9: ( M . ( F . ( 0 ) ) ) < ( +infty ) by A3,XXREAL_0:9;
now
let n;
( dom ( M * F ) ) = ( NAT ) by FUNCT_2:def 1;
then A10: (( ( M * F ) . n ) = ( M . ( F . n ) ) & ( ( M * F ) . ( n + 1 ) ) = ( M . ( F . ( n + 1 ) ) )) by FUNCT_1:12;
( F . ( n + 1 ) ) c= ( F . n ) by A6,PROB_2:6;
hence ( ( P1 * ASeq ) . ( n + 1 ) ) <= ( ( P1 * ASeq ) . n ) by A10,MEASURE1:31;
end;
then A11: ( P1 * ASeq ) is  non-increasing by SEQM_3:def 9;
then ( lim ( P1 * ASeq ) ) = ( lower_bound ( P1 * ASeq ) ) by A7,RINFSUP1:25
.= ( inf ( rng ( M * F ) ) ) by A7,CKB16:1;
then ( lim ( P1 * ASeq ) ) = ( M . ( meet ( rng F ) ) ) by A8,A9,MEASURE3:12
.= ( P1 . ( Intersection ASeq ) ) by SETLIM_1:8;
hence thesis by A7,A11;
end;
A12: (for A,B being (Event of S) holds (A misses B implies ( P1 . ( A \/ B ) ) = ( ( P1 . A ) + ( P1 . B ) )))
proof
