( P1 . ( A \/ B ) ) = ( ( M . A2 ) + ( M . B2 ) ) by A13,MEASURE1:30
.= ( ( P1 . A ) + ( P1 . B ) ) by SUPINF_2:1;
hence thesis;
end;
((for A being (Event of S) holds ( 0 ) <= ( P1 . A )) & ( P1 . X ) = 1) by A1,MEASURE1:def 2,MEASURE6:def 1;
